sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Browser as "Local browser/test client"
    participant LocalDev as "BlogAI.Web /local-dev"
    participant StatusService as "IBlogAiLocalAuthStatusService"
    participant Consumer as "IBlogAiAuthConsumerService"
    participant ApiClient as "IBlogAiLocalAuthApiClient"
    participant LocalApi as "Adventures.Auth.LocalApi /auth/login"
    participant Rendered as "Rendered display-safe status"

    Browser->>LocalDev: GET /local-dev
    LocalDev->>StatusService: GetStatusAsync(authPath: null)
    StatusService->>Consumer: Evaluate in-process baseline decisions
    Consumer-->>StatusService: Denied/hidden and allowed/shown decisions
    StatusService-->>LocalDev: Display-safe baseline model
    LocalDev-->>Rendered: In-process label, placeholder states, correlation metadata
    Rendered-->>Browser: 200 OK

    Browser->>LocalDev: GET /local-dev?authPath=api-client
    LocalDev->>StatusService: GetStatusAsync(authPath: "api-client")
    StatusService->>ApiClient: LoginAsync without local dev credential
    ApiClient->>LocalApi: POST /auth/login
    LocalApi-->>ApiClient: Display-safe denied decision
    StatusService->>ApiClient: LoginAsync with local/dev credential held in service layer
    ApiClient->>LocalApi: POST /auth/login
    LocalApi-->>ApiClient: Display-safe allowed decision
    ApiClient-->>StatusService: API-backed diagnostic decisions
    StatusService-->>LocalDev: Display-safe API-client diagnostic model
    LocalDev-->>Rendered: API-client label, no-fallback note, placeholder states, correlation metadata
    Rendered-->>Browser: 200 OK

    Note over LocalDev,Consumer: Default /local-dev remains in-process baseline
    Note over LocalDev,ApiClient: API client path runs only when authPath=api-client is explicit
    Note over StatusService,Rendered: API-client failure would render diagnostic failure without silent fallback
    Note over Browser,Rendered: Raw credential, token, secret, header, bearer, and password values are not rendered
    Note over Browser,LocalApi: No production deployment, OAuth/OpenID/RBAC, persistence/database, BlogEngine.NET coupling, real login UI, cookies/session topology, or auth middleware
